Hi,

Take a look at

  Earliest uses of mathematical words
  http://members.aol.com/jeff570/mathword.html

It doesn't say all that much, but note that something 'integral' is
whole, or undivided... which is really how we think of integers, as
opposed to rational numbers.  

Does this help? 

